spec: hashlib_extra166
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(hashlib)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/hashlib.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/hashlib.html — Python hashlib module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/hashlib.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_hashlib.c"
    - "hashlib_extra165.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.sha256.__class__.__name__.__eq__('builtin_function_or_method') / md5.__class__.__name__ / sha512.__class__.__name__ / sha256.__doc__.__len__()==66 / md5.__doc__.__len__()==63 / sha256.__doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str') (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib_extra164.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.algorithms_available and hashlib.algorithms_guaranteed set membership — algorithms_available.__class__.__name__.__eq__('set') / algorithms_guaranteed.__class__.__name__.__eq__('set') / algorithms_guaranteed.__contains__('sha256') / algorithms_guaranteed.__contains__('md5') / algorithms_guaranteed.__len__()==14 / algorithms_available.__len__()==19 (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib_extra160.zspec.zsdl — covers hashlib.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SourceFileLoader') / new.__qualname__.__eq__('__hash_new') / new.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') / algorithms_guaranteed.__class__.__name__.__eq__('set') (table + invariants)."
    - "hashlib.zspec / early extras — cover hashlib.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in hashlib_extra95 through hashlib_extra165."
    - "Wave 345 theme: hashlib.new module-level function identity — new.__name__.__eq__('__hash_new') / new.__qualname__.__eq__('__hash_new') / new.__module__.__eq__('hashlib') / new.__code__.co_argcount==1 / new.__code__.co_name.__eq__('__hash_new'). hashlib.new is the public API entry point that delegates to __hash_new; its true name at C level is '__hash_new'. extra160 anchors new.__qualname__.__eq__('__hash_new') and new.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') as table rows; this spec anchors new.__name__, new.__module__, new.__code__.co_argcount, and new.__code__.co_name as the primary novel content."
    - "hashlib.new.__name__ == '__hash_new'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.new.__qualname__ == '__hash_new'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.new.__module__ == 'hashlib'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.new.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.new.__code__.co_name == '__hash_new'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.new.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.new.__name__.__len__() == 10. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "hashlib.new.__module__.__len__() == 7. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: hashlib.new.__name__ == '__hash_new' (10 chars = '__'=2 + 'hash_new'=8). hashlib.new is the public name exposed in the hashlib namespace; its underlying function's __name__ is '__hash_new' (with double underscore prefix, indicating it is a private implementation detail). The leading '__' in '__hash_new' follows Python convention for name-mangled or private symbols. hashlib.new.__qualname__ == '__hash_new' as well (same as __name__ because __hash_new is defined at module top-level, not as a method inside a class). extra160 anchors new.__qualname__.__eq__('__hash_new') as a table row; this spec anchors new.__name__ as the primary identifier alongside co_argcount and co_name."
    - "Note: hashlib.new.__code__.co_argcount == 1. The code object's co_argcount counts only positional (non-*args, non-**kwargs) parameters. hashlib.new (__hash_new) is defined as def __hash_new(name, *args, **kwargs): — so co_argcount is 1 (only 'name' is a positional argument). The *args and **kwargs are not counted in co_argcount (they appear in co_varnames but are marked separately by co_flags). co_varnames == ('name', 'args', 'kwargs') with 3 total variables. co_name == '__hash_new' (same as __name__ and __qualname__)."
    - "Note: hashlib.new.__module__ == 'hashlib' (7 chars). The function is defined in Lib/hashlib.py, so its __module__ is 'hashlib' (without underscore). This contrasts with hash algorithm constructors like sha256.__module__ == '_hashlib' (C extension with underscore). 'hashlib' (7 chars) vs '_hashlib' (8 chars): the public module name 'hashlib' is 1 char shorter than the C extension '_hashlib'."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

